# =============================================================================
# AcousticSpace — Frontend Environment Variable Template
#
# Copy this file to .env before running the frontend dev server:
#   cp .env.example .env          # macOS / Linux
#   copy .env.example .env        # Windows
#
# The .env file is gitignored and must never be committed.  [NFR-5.4]
# All variables below have safe defaults for local development.
#
# IMPORTANT: Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the browser
# bundle.  Variables without this prefix remain server-side only.
# These values are baked into the JS bundle at build time — changing them
# after running `npm run build` has no effect.  [TDD §16.5]
# =============================================================================

# Base URL for all API calls made by the Axios client.
#
# How this value is used:
#   - Local dev (npm run dev): Vite proxy rewrites /api/* → http://localhost:8000/*
#     so this default of /api works without any extra configuration.  [DEPL-10]
#   - Docker Compose (production): Nginx proxies /api/* → http://backend:8000/*
#     so the same default of /api still works with no code change.  [DEPL-9]
#
# Only change this if you are pointing the frontend at a remote backend URL,
# e.g. VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.myserver.com
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
